flowchart TB
  %% Diagram 70: Incident Detection, Alerting, and On-Call Response Workflow

  Trigger[Alert threshold breach\nSLO/SLA or error spike]
  Notify[Notify on-call responder]
  Triage[Initial triage]
  Severity{Severity level?}

  Low[Low severity handling]
  High[High severity incident bridge]
  Mitigate[Mitigation actions]
  Verify[Recovery verification]
  Resolved{Service restored?}
  TimeGate{Recovered within response time window?}

  Escalate[Escalate to broader response team]
  Tune[Close as false positive and tune alert rule]
  PIR[Post-incident review and action items]
  Close[Incident closed with action tracking]

  Trigger --> Notify --> Triage --> Severity
  Severity -- Low --> Low --> Mitigate
  Severity -- High --> High --> Mitigate

  Mitigate --> Verify --> Resolved
  Resolved -- Yes --> TimeGate
  TimeGate -- Yes --> PIR --> Close
  TimeGate -- No --> Escalate --> Mitigate
  Resolved -- No --> Escalate --> Mitigate

  Triage -->|False positive| Tune --> Close
